==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: corporate raider
<hw>corporate raider</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Finance)</fld> <def>a
person who purchases or attempts to purchase a controlling interest in a
publicly-traded company against the wishes of the current
management.</def> <note>such a buyout is caled a <er>hostile
takeover</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> buyout specialist, takeover artist.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corporation</ent>⟦br⟧
